{"title_page": "Theodosia Harris", "text_new": "{{short description|American screenwriter}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Theodosia Harris\n| image              = The-House-of-a-Thousand-Scandals-Ad.jpg\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = June 2, 1877\n| birth_place        = [[Virginia City, Nevada]], USA\n| death_date         = {{death date and age|1938|11|22|1877|6|2}}\n| death_place        = [[San Antonio, Texas]], USA\n| occupation         = Screenwriter\n| years_active       = 1913\u20131916\n| spouse             = James Knowles\n}}\n\n'''Theodosia Harris''' was an American screenwriter active at the dawn of Hollywood's silent era. She worked as the chief scenario writer at Mutual for director [[David Horsley]] in the 1910s, penning dozens of short scenarios she was credited for (and probably many others she wasn't named on).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newspapers.com/image/425704883/?terms=%22theodosia+harris%22|title=14 Mar 1916, 2 - The Dodge City Daily Globe at Newspapers.com|website=Newspapers.com|language=en|access-date=2019-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newspapers.com/image/425704522/?terms=%22theodosia+harris%22|title=28 Feb 1916, 2 - The Dodge City Daily Globe at Newspapers.com|website=Newspapers.com|language=en|access-date=2019-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=saMbAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA249&lpg=PA249&dq=%22theodosia+harris%22+writer&source=bl&ots=Gdr6XjshSR&sig=ACfU3U25xYDxfTZNdoxwGjBrmpbPTAJR7w&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiY9bumgoXhAhWHv54KHW88C1QQ6AEwB3oECAEQAQ#v=onepage&q=%22theodosia%20harris%22%20writer&f=false|title=The Moving Picture World|date=1916|publisher=World Photographic Publishing Company|language=en}}</ref> She appears to have retired from screenwriting after marrying San Francisco businessman James Knowles in 1915.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6AtKAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA892&lpg=PA892&dq=%22theodosia+harris%22+writer&source=bl&ots=3bwNZe7iU2&sig=ACfU3U17M3Bg59si9XX5uMUaSaeMiE5RLg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiY9bumgoXhAhWHv54KHW88C1QQ6AEwCHoECAIQAQ#v=onepage&q=%22theodosia%20harris%22%20writer&f=false|title=Motography|date=1916|language=en}}</ref> She was involved in a 1917 [[Supreme Court of the United States|Supreme Court]] lawsuit over her scenario ''[[The House of a Thousand Scandals]]'', and she was never credited on another film after that.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kRieBITnPH8C&pg=RA1-PA205&lpg=RA1-PA205&dq=%22theodosia+harris%22&source=bl&ots=Hf0wY0ZMx9&sig=ACfU3U2N4jsfZo2jr_nlRXGkVPD5plquKg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiHsqbagIXhAhUnGTQIHWT0C_g4ChDoATAFegQIBBAB#v=onepage&q=%22theodosia%20harris%22&f=false|title=Supreme Court Apellate Division First Department|date=1917|language=en}}</ref> She died in San Antonio, Texas, in 1938.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://php.fold3.com/document/91068078/|title=Knowles, Theodosia Harris \u203a Knowles, Theodosia Harris - Fold3.com|website=Fold3|language=en|access-date=2019-03-15}}</ref>\n\n== Selected filmography ==\n\n* ''[[The Trap (1916 film)|The Trap]]'' (1916) \n* ''[[The Leopard's Bride]]'' (1916)\n* ''[[The Hidden Law]]'' (1916) \n* ''[[The Heart of Tara]]'' (1916)\n* ''[[The Soul's Cycle]]'' (1916)\n* ''[[Marta of the Jungles]]'' (1915)\n* ''[[The Terror of the Fold]]'' (1915)\n* ''[[The Arab's Vengeance]]'' (1915)\n* ''[[Martyrs of the Alamo]]'' (1915)\n* ''[[The House of a Thousand Scandals]]'' (1915)\n* ''[[The Day of Reckoning (film)|The Day of Reckoning]]'' (1915) \n* ''[[Competition (1915 film)|Competition]]'' (1915)\n* [[The Echo (1915 film)|''The Echo'']] (1915)\n* ''[[The Terror of the Fold]]'' (1915) (uncredited)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newspapers.com/image/473280204/?terms=%22theodosia+harris%22|title=13 Feb 1916, 47 - The Salt Lake Herald-Republican at Newspapers.com|website=Newspapers.com|language=en|access-date=2019-03-15}}</ref>\n* ''[[The Love Pirate]]'' (1915)\n* ''[[Coals of Fire]]'' (1915)\n* ''[[This Is th' Life]]'' (1914)\n* ''[[The Widow (1914 film)|The Widow]]'' (1914)\n* ''[[Youth and Art]]'' (1914)\n* ''[[The Independence of Susan]]'' (1914)\n* ''[[A Happy Coersion|A Happy Coercion]]'' (1914)\n* ''[[The Lost Treasure (1914)|The Lost Treasure]]'' (1914)\n* ''[[Fooling Uncle]]'' (1914)\n* ''[[Fate's Round-Up]]'' (1913) \n* ''[[Spartan Girl of the West]]'' (1913)<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xg8DAAAAYAAJ&pg=RA41-PA564&lpg=RA41-PA564&dq=%22theodosia+harris%22&source=bl&ots=mQHOX0EolV&sig=ACfU3U3KveMs0gd7neYEm8wOovDMIkEoNQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiHsqbagIXhAhUnGTQIHWT0C_g4ChDoATAHegQIAhAB#v=onepage&q=%22theodosia%20harris%22&f=false|title=Catalog of Copyright Entries: Works of art...|date=1918|publisher=Library of Congress, Copyright Office.|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''[[Flesh of His Flesh]]'' (1913) \n* ''[[Her Innocent Marriage]]'' (1913)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OZWiCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA244&lpg=PA244&dq=%22theodosia+harris%22&source=bl&ots=YhY-fH5ShC&sig=ACfU3U0Hg3miWmp-PvD9goZrZXc-ocLPLQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiHsqbagIXhAhUnGTQIHWT0C_g4ChDoATAIegQIARAB#v=onepage&q=%22theodosia%20harris%22&f=false|title=Wallace Reid: The Life and Death of a Hollywood Idol|last=Fleming|first=E. J.|date=2013-10-25|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9780786477258|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''[[The Kiss (1914 film)|The Kiss]]'' (1913)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* ''[[Youth and Jealousy]]'' (1913)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDB name|0365381}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Harris, Theodosia}}\n[[Category:Women film pioneers]]\n[[Category:American women screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from Nevada]]\n[[Category:1877 births]]\n[[Category:1938 deaths]]\n\n\n{{US-screen-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American screenwriter}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Theodosia Harris\n| image              = The-House-of-a-Thousand-Scandals-Ad.jpg\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = June 2, 1877\n| bir