ng Comes Out as Transgender|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 8, 2016|accessdate=March 8, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309103728/https://variety.com/2016/film/news/andy-wachowski-transgender-lilly-1201725853/|archivedate=March 9, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"wired\">{{cite magazine |last=Miller |first=Mark |title=Matrix Revelations |url=https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/11.11/matrix.html |magazine=[[Wired News]] |date=November 11, 2003 |accessdate=July 19, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120724022612/http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/11.11/matrix.html |archivedate=July 24, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"worldballoon\">{{cite web |first=John |last=Siuntres |title=Word Balloon The Pop Culture Interview Podcast: Word Balloon Podcast Geof Darrow's Shaolin Cowboy & Chris Roberson & Dennis Culver's Edison Rex |url=http://wordballoon.blogspot.com/2014/01/word-balloon-podcast-geof-darrows.html |publisher=wordballoon (blog) |accessdate=October 1, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006074626/http://wordballoon.blogspot.com/2014/01/word-balloon-podcast-geof-darrows.html |archivedate=October 6, 2014 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|The Wachowskis}}\n* {{IMDb name|905154|Lana Wachowski}}\n* {{IMDb name|905152|Lilly Wachowski}}\n\n{{The Wachowskis}}\n{{Saturn Award for Best Director}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wachowski}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women writers]]\n[[Category:Action film directors]]\n[[Category:American comics writers]]\n[[Category:American film producers]]\n[[Category:American people of Polish descent]]\n[[Category:American video game directors]]\n[[Category:American women film directors]]\n[[Category:American women screenwriters]]\n[[Category:English-lan